# API Design

**Normative contract:** `api/openapi.yaml`. **`docs/api_design.md`** is the narrative summary; when API policy or behavior changes, update **OpenAPI, handlers, and both docs** together so clients and codegen stay accurate.

## Base URL and versioning

- Product routes under **`/api/v1`**; **`GET /api/v1`** returns deployment metadata (`extensionsEnabled`, endpoints, etc.).
- **`/health`** and **`/api/v1/health`** for liveness (no auth).
- Version changes are explicit path revisions (e.g. future `v2`); do not silently change `v1` semantics.

## Resource naming and URL shape

- Plural segments: `playlists`, `playlist-groups`, `channels`, `playlist-items`.
- Kebab-case multi-word paths; single resource **`{id}`** path param = UUID **or** slug.
- Registry: **`GET`** / **`PUT`** `/api/v1/registry/channels` (PUT authenticated).

## JSON

- **`application/json`**; field names follow handler/DP-1 JSON tags and OpenAPI schemas (e.g. list: `items`, `hasMore`, optional `cursor`).

## ETag (conditional GET)

- **Single-resource GETs** (`GET` one playlist, playlist-group, channel, or playlist-item by id) return a strong **`ETag`** (SHA-256 of UTF-8 JSON body) and honor **`If-None-Match`** with **`304`** when unchanged. See `docs/api_design.md` and OpenAPI.
- **List GETs, registry GET, health/metadata:** no **`ETag`** in API v1 unless a future spec revision adds it.

## Authentication

- **Bearer API key** on all mutating routes, **or** (for POST and document PUT/PATCH on playlists, playlist-groups, channels) **signature-only** when the JSON body has a non-empty `signatures` array—see `SignatureOrAPIKeyAuth` in `internal/httpserver/middleware.go`.
- Registry PUT and DELETE routes require API key only (`APIKeyAuth`).
- Constant-time comparison of full header value vs configured secret when the Bearer path is used.
- Reads public unless network-restricted; no built-in OAuth.

## Pagination, sort, filter

- **`limit`:** 1–100, default 100. **`cursor`:** opaque. **`sort`:** `asc`|`desc` by `created_at`, default `asc`.
- **`playlist-items` and `playlists` lists:** query `channel` or `playlist-group` (UUID/slug); mutually exclusive where enforced. Channel filter on `GET /api/v1/playlists` follows extensions policy (404 `extensions_disabled` when extensions off).

## Error model

- Body shape: `{"error":"<stable_code>","message":"<detail>"}` — see `internal/httpserver/errors.go`.
- Typical codes: `bad_request`, `validation_error`, `signature_invalid` (400); `unauthorized` (401); `not_found`, `extensions_disabled` (404); `internal_error` (500).
- Prefer branching on **`error`**; **`message`** may vary.

## HTTP semantics (summary)

- POST create, GET read/list, PUT full replace, PATCH partial update, DELETE remove (per OpenAPI per resource).
- Registry PUT replaces the **entire** registry atomically.
- Extensions off: channel-style routes → **404** + `extensions_disabled`.

## Idempotency

- No idempotency-key header; POST may duplicate on retry; GET/DELETE retries are usual; PUT/PATCH are last-write-wins.

## Compatibility

- Avoid breaking OpenAPI without version or client migration plan; additive changes preferred.

